__comment0: Welcome to Minecraft lore day part two! So, there is a lot of water and a lot of different water types in Minecraft
__comment1: We are going to make a distinction between 'cold', 'cool', 'normal' and 'hot' water.
__comment2: - Hot water is going to be in oceans, savannas, mesas, and deserts
__comment3: - Cold water is going to be wherever freezing happens, so ice plains, frozen rivers etc
__comment4: - Cool water is going to be in the mountainous areas
__comment5: - Everywhere else it's normal water, except for sky and void, where water is room temperature because yes
__comment6: If you have any other ideas, please let me know
__comment7: Regarding levels, on the other hand, we take a weighted average of the form ((level * waterTemp) + ((maxLevels - level) * roomTemp)) / maxLevels
__comment8: In the above, level is defined as (7 - valueOf(levelProperty))
